1.body: All messages broadcasted by Mostro daemon are Parameterized Replaceable Events and use 30078 as event kind, a list of standard event kinds can be found here

12.body:
Buyer sends the LN invoice to Mostro. { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": null, "action": "AddInvoice", "content": { "PaymentRequest": [ null, "lnbcrt78510n1pj59wmepp50677g8tffdqa2p8882y0x6newny5vtz0hjuyngdwv226nanv4uzsdqqcqzzsxqyz5vqsp5skn973360gp4yhlpmefwvul5hs58lkkl3u3ujvt57elmp4zugp4q9qyyssqw4nzlr72w28k4waycf27qvgzc9sp79sqlw83j56txltz4va44j7jda23ydcujj9y5k6k0rn5ms84w8wmcmcyk5g3mhpqepf7envhdccp72nz6e" ] } }
} Now both parties have an Active order and they can keep going with the trade.

13.title: Seller pays hold invoice

14.body: Mostro clients should use ephemeral keys to communicate with Mostro, indicating the pubkey where they want to be contacted in the pubkey field of the message, this way orders and users can't be easily linked, buyer_pubkey and seller_pubkey fields are each party real pubkeys.
14.breadcrumbs: Seller pays hold invoice » Ephemeral keys
14.title: Ephemeral keys

15.body:
After the buyer sends the fiat money to the seller, the buyer should send a message to Mostro indicating that the fiat money was sent, the message will look like this: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": null, "action": "FiatSent", "content": null }
}
15.title: Fiat sent

16.title: Mostro response

17.body:
After confirming the buyer sent the fiat money, the seller should send a message to Mostro indicating that sats should be delivered to the buyer, the message will look like this: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": "npub1qqqxssz4k6swex94zdg5s4pqx3uqlhwsc2vdzvhjvzk33pcypkhqe9aeq2", "action": "Release", "content": null }
}
17.title: Release

18.title: Mostro response

19.body:
Right after seller release sats Mostro will try to pay the buyer's lightning invoice, if the payment is successful Mostro will send a message to the buyer indicating that the purchase was completed: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": null, "action": "PurchaseCompleted", "content": null }
}
19.title: Buyer receives sats

2.body:
All messages from/to Mostro should be a Nostr event kind 4 , the content field of the event should be a base64-encoded, aes-256-cbc encrypted JSON-serialized string (with no white space or line breaks) of the following structure: version: Version of the protocol, currently 1 pubkey (optional): Real pubkey of the user, if present the message is signed with the real pubkey (TBD), this is used when users are sending messages from ephemeral keys action : Action to be performed by Mostro daemon content (optional): Content of the message, this field is optional and depends on the action These fields are relative to the wrapper, here an example of a FiatSent Order message, in this case id is the Order Id: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": "npub1qqq...", "action": "FiatSent", "content": null }
}
2.breadcrumbs: Home » Communication between users and Mostro
2.title: Communication between users and Mostro

20.title: User rating

21.body:
If Mostro received the correct message, it will send back a confirmation message to the user with Action: RateReceived: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "7e44aa5d-855a-4b17-865e-8ca3834a91a3", "pubkey": null, "action": "RateReceived", "content": null }
}
21.title: Confirmation message

22.body:
A user can cancel an Order created by himself and with status Pending sending action Cancel, the message will look like this: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": "npub1qqqt938cer4dvlslg04zwwf66ts8r3txp6mv79cx2498pyuqx8uq0c7qkj", "action": "Cancel", "content": null }
}
22.title: Cancel Order

23.body:
Mostro will send a message with action Cancel confirming the order was canceled, here an example of the message: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": null, "action": "Cancel", "content": null }
}
23.title: Mostro response

24.title: Cancel cooperatively

25.body:
A use can start a dispute in an order with status Pending or FiatSent sending action Dispute, here is an example where the seller initiates a dispute: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": "npub1qqqt938cer4dvlslg04zwwf66ts8r3txp6mv79cx2498pyuqx8uq0c7qkj", "action": "Dispute", "content": null }
}
25.title: Dispute

26.title: Mostro response

28.body:
Action is used to identify each message between Mostro and users pub enum Action { Order, TakeSell, TakeBuy, PayInvoice, FiatSent, Release, Cancel, CooperativeCancelInitiatedByYou, CooperativeCancelInitiatedByPeer, DisputeInitiatedByYou, DisputeInitiatedByPeer, CooperativeCancelAccepted, BuyerInvoiceAccepted, SaleCompleted, PurchaseCompleted, HoldInvoicePaymentAccepted, HoldInvoicePaymentSettled, HoldInvoicePaymentCanceled, WaitingSellerToPay, WaitingBuyerInvoice, AddInvoice, BuyerTookOrder, RateUser, CantDo, Received, Dispute, AdminCancel, AdminSettle, AdminAddSolver, AdminTakeDispute,
} You can see details in mostro core documentation
28.title: mostro_core::Action

3.body:
To create a new sell order the user should send a Nostr event kind 4 to Mostro with the following content: { "Order": { "version": "1", "pubkey": "npub1qqq...", "action": "NewOrder", "content": { "Order": { "kind": "Sell", "status": "Pending", "amount": 0, "fiat_code": "VES", "fiat_amount": 100, "payment_method": "face to face", "premium": 1, "created_at": 0 } } }
} Let's explain some of the fields: kind: Sell or Buy status: Is always Pending when creating a new order amount: 0 for when we want to sell with at market price, otherwise the amount in satoshis pubkey: Real user's npub, we use this when the message was sent from an ephemeral key created_at: No need to send the correct unix timestamp, Mostro will replace it with the current time
3.breadcrumbs: Creating an order » Creating a new order
3.title: Creating a new order

4.body:
Mostro will send back a confirmation message to the user like the following: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": "npub1qqq...", "action": "NewOrder", "content": { "Order": { "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "kind": "Sell", "status": "Pending", "amount": 0, "fiat_code": "VES", "fiat_amount": 100, "payment_method": "face to face", "premium": 1, "created_at": 1698870173 } } }
}
4.title: Confirmation message

5.body:
If the order amount is 0 the buyer don't know the exact amount to create the invoice, buyer will send a message in a Nostr event kind 4 to Mostro with the following content: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": "npub1qqq...", "action": "TakeSell", "content": null }
}
5.breadcrumbs: Take sell » Taking a sell order
5.title: Taking a sell order

6.body:
In order to continue the buyer needs to send a lightning network invoice to Mostro, in this case the amount of the order is 0, so Mostro will need to calculate the amount of sats for this order, then Mostro will send back a message asking for a LN invoice indicating the correct amount of sats that the invoice should have: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": null, "action": "AddInvoice", "content": { "Order": { "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "amount": 7851, "fiat_code": "VES", "fiat_amount": 100, "payment_method": "face to face", "premium": 1, "buyer_pubkey": null, "seller_pubkey": null } } }
}
6.title: Mostro response

7.body:
Here is how the buyer send the LN invoice to Mostro, in case the order has a fixed sats amount, the buyer can we skip the previous step: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": null, "action": "TakeSell", "content": { "PaymentRequest": [ null, "lnbcrt78510n1pj59wmepp50677g8tffdqa2p8882y0x6newny5vtz0hjuyngdwv226nanv4uzsdqqcqzzsxqyz5vqsp5skn973360gp4yhlpmefwvul5hs58lkkl3u3ujvt57elmp4zugp4q9qyyssqw4nzlr72w28k4waycf27qvgzc9sp79sqlw83j56txltz4va44j7jda23ydcujj9y5k6k0rn5ms84w8wmcmcyk5g3mhpqepf7envhdccp72nz6e" ] } }
}
7.breadcrumbs: Take sell » Buyer sends LN invoice
7.title: Buyer sends LN invoice

8.body:
Mostro send the following message to the buyer: { "Order": { "version": "1", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "pubkey": null, "action": "WaitingSellerToPay", "content": null }
}
8.title: Mostro response

9.body:
To take an order the seller will send to Mostro a message with the following content: { "Order": { "version": "1", "pubkey": "npub1qqqxssz4k6swex94zdg5s4pqx3uqlhwsc2vdzvhjvzk33pcypkhqe9aeq2", "id": "ede61c96-4c13-4519-bf3a-dcf7f1e9d842", "action": "TakeBuy", "content": null }
}
